{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ψῡχρός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> <b>cold,</b> χάλαζα, νιφάδες, χιών, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.171, 19.358, 22.152 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ψ. χαλκός (as we say '<b>cold</b> steel') [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5.75: frequently of water, ψ. ὕδωρ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.392, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.49 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ψυχρόν (without ὕδωρ) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 263; λοῦνται ψυχρῷ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.37; ἀναγαργαρίζεσθαι ψυχρῷ “IG” 42(1).126.30 (Epid., 2nd c.AD) (but τὸ ψυχρὸν\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] also ={ψῦχος}, <b>cold,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.142); ψ. ὥστε λούσασθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.13.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: of the air, αὔρη ψ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.469; αἰθήρ 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.88 (assuming variant); νύκτες 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.87; κυνὸς ψυχρὰ δύσις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 432.11 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ψ. βίος life <b>in the cold,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 263: especially of dead things, νέκυς (opposed to θερμὸν αἷμα) 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 622 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>cold</b> meats, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 173.4, etc. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of a snake, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.58 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-ότερος</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.22, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 24b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-ότατος</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 1.41. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>ineffectual, vain,</b> ἐπικουρίη ψ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.108; ἐπαρθεὶς ψυχρῇ νίκῃ [prev. author] 9.49; ψ. παραγκάλισμα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 650 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θερμὴν ἐπὶ ψυχροῖσι καρδίαν ἔχεις a hot spirit in <b>a cold business,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 88. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of feelings, ψ. τέρψις, ἐλπίς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 353, “IA” 1014. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of persons, <b>cold-hearted, heartless, indifferent,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.4.22, 23; ψ. καὶ μελαγχολικοί 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Magna Moralia” 1203b1; ἐκ σιδάρου κεχάλκευται μέλαιναν καρδίαν ψυχρᾷ φλογί 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 123.5; οὔτε ψ. εἶ οὔτε ζεστός NT.Rev.3.15. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> of <b>flat, lifeless, insipid</b> productions, τὸν Παλαμήδην (the play so named) ψυχρὸν ὄντ᾽ αἰσχύνεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 848; σκῶμμα.. σφόδρα ψ. 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 244 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ψ. καὶ ἀηδὴς [Μοῦσα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 802d; ἕωλα καὶ ψ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.112; πρᾶγμα.. φρέατος.. ψυχρότερον Ἀραρότος 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 179, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1405b34, 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 114, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence jokes in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 138 - 140, Machoap. 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 13.580a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of authors themselves, γίνεται ψυχρός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Isocrate” 3 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i>, ὁ δ᾽ αὖ Θέογνις ψυχρὸς ὢν ψυχρῶς ποιεῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 170 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκώψαντι ψ. ἐπιγελάσαι to laugh at a <b>feeble</b> joke, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 2.4; τοὺς γοῦν ψυχροὺς ψ. λέγουσι διαλέγεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 284e. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>silly,</b> γραϊδίοις ψυχροῖς ὁμιλοῦντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Epistulae” 89b. [Written ψυχθρός “IG” 12(5).1104 (Syros, 2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; compare conversely μάκρα for μάκτρα (ψυχρός originally 'cooled by blowing' from ψύχω 'blow').]","strongNumber":"G5593","accentedUnicode":"ψυχρός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0404","matchingForm":"ἀναψύχω","stepTransliteration":"anapsuchō","gloss":"to refresh","_zh_tw_Gloss":"暢快","_es_Gloss":"refrescar","_zh_Gloss":"畅快"},{"strongNumber":"G2711","matchingForm":"καταψύχω","stepTransliteration":"katapsuchō","gloss":"to cool","_zh_tw_Gloss":"涼涼","_es_Gloss":"enfriar","_zh_Gloss":"凉凉"},{"strongNumber":"G5592","matchingForm":"ψῦχος","stepTransliteration":"psuchos","gloss":"cold","_zh_tw_Gloss":"寒冷","_es_Gloss":"frío","_zh_Gloss":"寒冷"},{"strongNumber":"G5594","matchingForm":"ψύχω","stepTransliteration":"psuchō","gloss":"to cool","_zh_tw_Gloss":"就漸漸冷淡了","_es_Gloss":"enfriar","_zh_Gloss":"就渐渐冷淡了"}],"shortDef":"cold","mediumDef":"<b>cool, cold,</b> <ref='Mat.10.42'>Mt. 10:42</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <ref='Rev.3.15, 16'>Rev. 3:15, 16</ref>*","stepGloss":"cold","stepTransliteration":"psuchros","count":4,"_es_Definition":"frío ; agua fría (MAT.10:42) ","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 冰冷的<br> 1a) 字意<br>  1a1) 冷的